The paper deals with improving the classification accuracy of a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for object recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of saliency as an attentional mechanism to guide the feature extraction process, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are performed on various fine-grained datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
